Privacy Policy

Last updated: 24 Jan. 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how Jellatrix (“the App”) handles user data.

⸻

1. Target Audience

The App is designed for a general audience, including children of all ages (0+).
The App contains no violence and features a colorful, cartoon-style presentation with a friendly character.

⸻

2. Information Collection

Local Data
The App stores local high scores on the user’s device only.
This data never leaves the device and is not shared with the developer or any third parties.

Online Leaderboards
The App offers optional online leaderboards through Google Play Games Services.
	•	Online features are available only if the user voluntarily signs in to Google Play.
	•	The App itself does not collect, store, or manage user account data.
	•	All data related to online leaderboards is handled by Google Play Games Services in accordance with Google’s privacy policies.

⸻

3. Advertising

The App displays advertisements provided by Google (for example, Google Ad services).
	•	Ads may be shown to users who have not purchased the ad-free option.
	•	Users can disable ads via an in-app purchase.
	•	Advertising services may collect limited data (such as device information) as required to serve ads, in accordance with Google’s own privacy policies and applicable laws.

The developer does not directly collect or store advertising data.

⸻

4. Children’s Privacy

The App complies with applicable children’s privacy regulations.
	•	The App does not knowingly collect personal information from children.
	•	The App does not include:
	•	user chat or social interaction
	•	user-generated content
	•	location tracking
	•	external links intended for children

Any third-party services used (such as Google Play Games Services or Google advertising) operate under their own privacy and family-friendly policies.

⸻

5. Data Sharing

The developer does not sell, trade, or share personal user data.

Any data processed by third-party services is governed by their respective privacy policies.

⸻

6. Data Security

The App does not store personal data on developer-controlled servers.
Local game data remains on the user’s device.

⸻

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated if the App’s functionality changes.
Updates will be published on this page.

